events.description: The Arian Vandal Kingdom ceases its persecution of Nicene Christianity.
events.html: • 484 – The Arian Vandal Kingdom ceases its persecution of Nicene Christianity.[1]

events.description: Chlothar I is crowned King of the Franks.
events.html: • 558 – Chlothar I is crowned King of the Franks.

events.description: Maya queen Yohl Ik'nal is crowned ruler of Palenque.
events.html: • 583 – Maya queen Yohl Ik'nal is crowned ruler of Palenque.

events.description: The Sack of Aleppo as part of the Arab–Byzantine wars: Under the future Emperor Nicephorus Phocas, Byzantine troops storm the city of Aleppo.
events.html: • 962 – The Sack of Aleppo as part of the Arab–Byzantine wars: Under the future Emperor Nicephorus Phocas, Byzantine troops storm the city of Aleppo.

events.description: Arauco War: Governor of Chile Martín García Óñez de Loyola is killed in the Battle of Curalaba by Mapuches led by Pelantaru.
events.html: • 1598 – Arauco War: Governor of Chile Martín García Óñez de Loyola is killed in the Battle of Curalaba by Mapuches led by Pelantaru.

events.description: As part of the Glorious Revolution, King James II of England flees from England to Paris, France after being deposed in favor of his son-in-law and nephew, William of Orange and his daughter Mary.
events.html: • 1688 – As part of the Glorious Revolution, King James II of England flees from England to Paris, France after being deposed in favor of his son-in-law and nephew, William of Orange and his daughter Mary.

events.description: Moscow State Academy of Choreography was founded under the reign of Catherine II. It is the second ballet school in Russia after Vaganova Academy of Russian Ballet.
events.html: • 1773 – Moscow State Academy of Choreography was founded[2] under the reign of Catherine II. It is the second ballet school in Russia after Vaganova Academy of Russian Ballet.

events.description: George Washington resigns as commander-in-chief of the Continental Army at the Maryland State House in Annapolis, Maryland.
events.html: • 1783 – George Washington resigns as commander-in-chief of the Continental Army at the Maryland State House in Annapolis, Maryland.

events.description: The Battle of Savenay: A decisive defeat of the royalist counter-revolutionaries in War in the Vendée during the French Revolution.
events.html: • 1793 – The Battle of Savenay: A decisive defeat of the royalist counter-revolutionaries in War in the Vendée during the French Revolution.

events.description: The novel Emma by Jane Austen is first published.
events.html: • 1815 – The novel Emma by Jane Austen is first published.

events.description: First day of the Constantinople Conference which resulted in agreement for political reforms in the Balkans.
events.html: • 1876 – First day of the Constantinople Conference which resulted in agreement for political reforms in the Balkans.

events.description: The opera Hansel and Gretel by Engelbert Humperdinck is first performed.
events.html: • 1893 – The opera Hansel and Gretel by Engelbert Humperdinck is first performed.

events.description: The Tampere conference, where Vladimir Lenin and Joseph Stalin meet for the first time, is held in Tampere, Finland.
events.html: • 1905 – The Tampere conference, where Vladimir Lenin and Joseph Stalin meet for the first time, is held in Tampere, Finland.[3]

events.description: The Federal Reserve Act is signed into law by President Woodrow Wilson, creating the Federal Reserve System.
events.html: • 1913 – The Federal Reserve Act is signed into law by President Woodrow Wilson, creating the Federal Reserve System.

events.description: World War I: Australian and New Zealand troops arrive in Cairo, Egypt.
events.html: • 1914 – World War I: Australian and New Zealand troops arrive in Cairo, Egypt.

events.description: World War I: During the Battle of Sarikamish, Ottoman forces mistook one another for Russian troops. The following friendly fire incident leaves 2,000 Ottomans dead and many more wounded.
events.html: • 1914 – World War I: During the Battle of Sarikamish, Ottoman forces mistook one another for Russian troops. The following friendly fire incident leaves 2,000 Ottomans dead and many more wounded.[4]

events.description: World War I: Battle of Magdhaba: Allied forces defeat Turkish forces in the Sinai Peninsula.
events.html: • 1916 – World War I: Battle of Magdhaba: Allied forces defeat Turkish forces in the Sinai Peninsula.

events.description: Sex Disqualification (Removal) Act 1919 becomes law in the United Kingdom.
events.html: • 1919 – Sex Disqualification (Removal) Act 1919 becomes law in the United Kingdom.

events.description: Colombia becomes a signatory to the Buenos Aires copyright treaty.
events.html: • 1936 – Colombia becomes a signatory to the Buenos Aires copyright treaty.

events.description: Spanish Civil War: The Spanish Republic legalizes the Regional Defence Council of Aragon.
events.html: • 1936 – Spanish Civil War: The Spanish Republic legalizes the Regional Defence Council of Aragon.[5]

events.description: World War II: After 15 days of fighting, the Imperial Japanese Army occupies Wake Island.
events.html: • 1941 – World War II: After 15 days of fighting, the Imperial Japanese Army occupies Wake Island.

events.description: The transistor is first demonstrated at Bell Laboratories.
events.html: • 1947 – The transistor is first demonstrated at Bell Laboratories.

events.description: Seven Japanese military and political leaders convicted of war crimes by the International Military Tribunal for the Far East are executed by Allied occupation authorities at Sugamo Prison in Tokyo, Japan.
events.html: • 1948 – Seven Japanese military and political leaders convicted of war crimes by the International Military Tribunal for the Far East are executed by Allied occupation authorities at Sugamo Prison in Tokyo, Japan.

entities.name: International Military Tribunal for the Far East

events.description: General Walton Walker dies in a jeep accident and is replaced by General Matthew Ridgway in the Eighth United States Army.
events.html: • 1950 – General Walton Walker dies in a jeep accident and is replaced by General Matthew Ridgway in the Eighth United States Army.[6]

events.description: First successful kidney transplant is performed by J. Hartwell Harrison and Joseph Murray.
events.html: • 1954 – First successful kidney transplant is performed by J. Hartwell Harrison and Joseph Murray.

events.description: The first film adaptation of Väinö Linna's novel The Unknown Soldier, directed by Edvin Laine, premieres.
events.html: • 1955 – The first film adaptation of Väinö Linna's novel The Unknown Soldier, directed by Edvin Laine, premieres.[7][8]

events.description: Hilkka Saarinen née Pylkkänen is murdered in the so-called "oven homicide" case in Krootila, Kokemäki, Finland.
events.html: • 1960 – Hilkka Saarinen née Pylkkänen is murdered in the so-called "oven homicide" case in Krootila, Kokemäki, Finland.[9]

events.description: The 82 sailors from the USS Pueblo are released after eleven months of internment in North Korea.
events.html: • 1968 – The 82 sailors from the USS Pueblo are released after eleven months of internment in North Korea.

events.description: The North Tower of the World Trade Center in Manhattan, New York, New York is topped out at 417 metres (1,368 ft), making it the tallest building in the world.
events.html: • 1970 – The North Tower of the World Trade Center in Manhattan, New York, New York is topped out at 417 metres (1,368 ft), making it the tallest building in the world.

entities.name: List of tenants in 1 World Trade Center (1971–2001)

events.description: The Democratic Republic of the Congo officially becomes a one-party state.
events.html: • 1970 – The Democratic Republic of the Congo officially becomes a one-party state.

events.description: The Immaculate Reception is caught by Franco Harris to win the Pittsburgh Steelers their first ever playoff victory, after defeating the Oakland Raiders.
events.html: • 1972 – The Immaculate Reception is caught by Franco Harris to win the Pittsburgh Steelers their first ever playoff victory, after defeating the Oakland Raiders.[10]

events.description: A 6.5 magnitude earthquake strikes the Nicaraguan capital of Managua killing more than 10,000.
events.html: • 1972 – A 6.5 magnitude earthquake strikes the Nicaraguan capital of Managua killing more than 10,000.

events.description: The 16 survivors of the Andes flight disaster are rescued after 73 days, surviving by cannibalism.
events.html: • 1972 – The 16 survivors of the Andes flight disaster are rescued after 73 days, surviving by cannibalism.

events.description: Alitalia Flight 4128 crashes into the Tyrrhenian Sea while on approach to Falcone Borsellino Airport in Palermo, Italy, killing 108.
events.html: • 1978 – Alitalia Flight 4128 crashes into the Tyrrhenian Sea while on approach to Falcone Borsellino Airport in Palermo, Italy, killing 108.[11]

events.description: Soviet–Afghan War: Soviet Union forces occupy Kabul, the Afghan capital.
events.html: • 1979 – Soviet–Afghan War: Soviet Union forces occupy Kabul, the Afghan capital.

events.description: After experiencing an engine fire, Aeroflot Flight 3519 attempts to make an emergency landing at Krasnoyarsk International Airport but crashes, killing 110 of the 111 people on board.
events.html: • 1984 – After experiencing an engine fire, Aeroflot Flight 3519 attempts to make an emergency landing at Krasnoyarsk International Airport but crashes, killing 110 of the 111 people on board.[12]

events.description: Voyager, piloted by Dick Rutan and Jeana Yeager, lands at Edwards Air Force Base in California becoming the first aircraft to fly non-stop around the world without aerial or ground refueling.
events.html: • 1986 – Voyager, piloted by Dick Rutan and Jeana Yeager, lands at Edwards Air Force Base in California becoming the first aircraft to fly non-stop around the world without aerial or ground refueling.

events.description: History of Slovenia: In a referendum, 88.5% of Slovenia's overall electorate vote for independence from Yugoslavia.
events.html: • 1990 – History of Slovenia: In a referendum, 88.5% of Slovenia's overall electorate vote for independence from Yugoslavia.

events.description: A U.S. MQ-1 Predator is shot down by an Iraqi MiG-25 in the first combat engagement between a drone and conventional aircraft.
events.html: • 2002 – A U.S. MQ-1 Predator is shot down by an Iraqi MiG-25 in the first combat engagement between a drone and conventional aircraft.

events.description: An explosion at the PetroChina Chuandongbei natural gas field in Kai County, Chongqing, China, kills at least 234.
events.html: • 2003 – An explosion at the PetroChina Chuandongbei natural gas field in Kai County, Chongqing, China, kills at least 234.

events.description: An Antonov An-140, Azerbaijan Airlines Flight 217 from Baku, Azerbaijan, to Aktau, Kazakhstan, heading across the Caspian Sea, crashes, killing 23 people.
events.html: • 2005 – An Antonov An-140, Azerbaijan Airlines Flight 217 from Baku, Azerbaijan, to Aktau, Kazakhstan, heading across the Caspian Sea, crashes, killing 23 people.[13]

events.description: An agreement is made for the Kingdom of Nepal to be abolished and the country to become a federal republic with the Prime Minister becoming head of state.
events.html: • 2007 – An agreement is made for the Kingdom of Nepal to be abolished and the country to become a federal republic with the Prime Minister becoming head of state.

events.description: A coup d'état occurs in Guinea hours after the death of President Lansana Conté.
events.html: • 2008 – A coup d'état occurs in Guinea hours after the death of President Lansana Conté.[14]
